{"comments":"Smoothing Types — ADTs for stroke smoothing and stabilization.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nStroke smoothing reduces input jitter for cleaner lines. Different\nalgorithms trade off between latency and smoothness. The SmoothingMode\nenum provides industry-standard approaches from raw input to adaptive\nfiltering.\n\n## Smoothing Modes\n\n- **NoSmoothing**: Raw input, zero latency\n- **BasicSmoothing**: Simple moving average\n- **PulledString**: Lazy cursor follows at a distance\n- **MovingAverage**: Weighted average over window\n- **ExponentialSmoothing**: Exponential decay weighting\n- **OneEuroFilter**: Adaptive filter (smooth when slow, responsive when fast)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[70,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Smoothing/Types.purs","start":[70,3]},"title":"NoSmoothing"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[71,19],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Smoothing/Types.purs","start":[71,3]},"title":"BasicSmoothing"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[72,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Smoothing/Types.purs","start":[72,3]},"title":"PulledString"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[73,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Smoothing/Types.purs","start":[73,3]},"title":"MovingAverage"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[74,25],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Smoothing/Types.purs","start":[74,3]},"title":"ExponentialSmoothing"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[75,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Smoothing/Types.purs","start":[75,3]},"title":"OneEuro